      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bloom the cocoa",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk the {{cocoa-powder}} into the hot {{black-coffee}} until smooth. Leave to cool to room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare and mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease two 20 cm round tins and line the bases. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} (for the cake) and {{light-brown-sugar}} together until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{free-range-eggs}} and {{vanilla-extract}}. Whisk the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} together. Fold the dry ingredients into the batter in three additions, alternating with the {{buttermilk}}. Stir in the cooled cocoa mixture until smooth.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 30 to 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the batter evenly between the tins. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tins for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack to cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the frosting and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{dark-chocolate}} in a bowl over barely simmering water. Leave to cool to room temperature. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} (for the frosting) until very pale and fluffy, about 4 minutes. Beat in the {{icing-sugar}} in two additions, then beat in the cooled chocolate and {{double-cream}} until smooth. Sandwich the cooled layers with a third of the frosting; spread the rest over the top and sides.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
